HOW TO GRUB
===========

0. Get fs_uuid


  Windows:


  grub-probe --target=fs_uuid esp/EFI/Microsoft/Boot/bootmgfw.efi

  Linux:


  grub-probe --target=fs_uuid esp/EFI/Linux/arch-linux-lts.efi

1. Add windows


  sudo nvim /etc/grub.d/40_custom

  add following line


  if [ "$grub_platform" = "efi" ]; then
    menuentry 'Microsoft Windows' --id 'microsoft-windows' {
      insmod part_gpt
      insmod fat
      search --no-floppy --set=root --fs-uuid <YOUR_EFI_UUID>
      chainloader /EFI/Microsoft/Boot/bootmgfw.efi
    }
  fi

  where esp is your EFI system mount location

2. Add UEFI firmware settings


  sudo nvim /etc/grub.d/40_custom

  add following line


  if [ "$grub_platform" = "efi" ]; then
    fwsetup --is-supported
    if [ "$?" = 0 ]; then
      menuentry 'Custom UEFI Firmware Settings' --id 'uefi-firmware' {
        fwsetup
      }
    fi
  fi

3. Custom chainload UKI
  by default UKI entries in GRUB doesn't show difference from one and another


  sudo nvim /etc/grub.d/40_custom

  add following line


  if [ "$grub_platform" = "efi" ]; then
    menuentry 'Your Linux' --id 'your-linux' {
      insmod fat
      insmod chain
      search --no-floppy --set=root --fs-uuid <YOUR_EFI_UUID>
      chainloader /EFI/Linux/<your_linux>.efi
    }
  fi

4. Disable script in /etc/grub.d


  sudo chmod -x /etc/grub.d/15_uki

